</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umindwarpan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindwarpan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 10:21:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> &quot;Also, what other tactics can we wizzies use to perform well in this type combat?&quot;<br>
<br>
Swap yourself out for a melee class. Casters are always primary targets because they can eliminate a player quickly. Large pvp battles usually depend on how long you can last in PvP. A caster is a sitting duck when he gets low on mana. You are far better off getting a meatshield instead for your team, unfortunately. These type of battle is not conducive to wizards at all. <br>
<br>
You can try the yonder/nuke approach, but with 18 opponents in an environment such as the arena, chances are you will be spotted and attacked by another melee before you can get a spell off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubuschbavarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Busch Bavarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/3/01 6:45:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ToT Strats?</span><hr size=1> That was what I feared you might say.  It sucks that I can waste a warrior without him even dropping my epic skin one-on-one, yet it appears that we won't be a viable option in ToT.<br>
